# internal/server/middleware

HTTP middleware chain for `{{ .Name }}`.

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `cors_middleware.go` | CORS headers and OPTIONS preflight — registered first so preflight bypasses auth |
| `trace_id_middleware.go` | Generates a unique `X-Trace-Id` per request and attaches it to the context |
| `logger_middleware.go` | Structured request/response logging via zap |
| `error_middleware.go` | Maps `errors.AppError` values to structured JSON error responses |
| `recovery_middleware.go` | Recovers from panics and returns a 500 response |

**Registration order** (in `cmd/server/server.go`):
```
CORS → TraceID → Logger → Recovery → ErrorMapper
```

**CORS production usage** — restrict origins explicitly:
```go
r.Use(middleware.CORS("https://app.example.com", "https://admin.example.com"))
```
